Read CLAUDE.md at the repo root before making changes — it is the operating
manual (architecture, commands, invariants, gotchas) for all agents, not just
Claude.

Critical constraints while working here:

- This repo is IN PRODUCTION: merging to `main` triggers deploys
  (Cloud Run API via OIDC + GitHub Pages UI). Work on branches.
- Use the Makefile: `make up` (local stack :8000/:5500), `make test`,
  `make lint` — CI runs these exact targets.
- Corpus data lives in the GCS bucket, never baked into Docker images; the
  Dockerfile's final stage must remain the Cloud Run runtime stage.
- All env/config access goes through `shared/settings.py` (pydantic-settings).
- Scoring-only text belongs in `RawArticle.content` (hidden), never in
  `summary` (rendered in the UI).
- Do not remove the rate limiter on `POST /extract/ttps` (it spends LLM
  credits); keep GitHub Actions SHA-pinned; never commit secrets
  (detect-secrets pre-commit hook enforces).
